- The cash sale of the balance of ABG in the first quarter of 2024 produced a **pretax gain of $414.8 million** (tax expense $103.7 million)【page_73】, whereas the equity‑dilution of SPARC Group in the third quarter of 2023 generated a **non‑cash pretax gain of $145.8 million**【page_73】. The ABG divestiture gain was therefore roughly three times larger than the SPARC dilution gain.

- ABG ownership was reduced in several steps during 2023 before the 2024 sale:  
  • Q2 2023 – dilution from ~12.3 % to ~11.8 % (non‑cash gain $36.4 m)【page_73】;  
  • Q3 2023 – dilution from ~11.8 % to ~11.7 % (non‑cash gain $12.4 m)【page_73】;  
  • Q4 2023 – dilution to ~9.6 % (non‑cash gain $10.3 m)【page_73】 and a cash sale of a portion of the stake (pre‑tax gain $157.1 m)【page_73】;  
  • Q1 2024 – sale of the remaining interest (cash proceeds $1.2 bn, pretax gain $414.8 m)【page_73】.  

Thus, the 2024 ABG divestiture yielded a far larger cash gain than the 2023 SPARC equity‑dilution gain, and ABG ownership was progressively trimmed from roughly 12 % in early 2023 to 0 % by the first quarter of 2024.
